  "detection": [
    {
      "id": "DS0022",
      "name": "File",
      "component": "File Metadata",
      "url": "/datasources/DS0022",
      "detects": "If the document is opened with a Graphical User Interface (GUI) the malicious p-code is decompiled and may be viewed. However, if the PROJECT stream, which specifies the project properties, is modified in a specific way the decompiled VBA code will not be displayed. For example, adding a module name that is undefined to the PROJECT stream will inhibit attempts of reading the VBA source code through the GUI.[1]"
    },
    {
      "id": "DS0012",
      "name": "Script",
      "component": "Script Execution",
      "url": "/datasources/DS0012",
      "detects": "Detection efforts should be placed finding differences between VBA source code and p-code. [4] VBA code can be extracted from p-code before execution with tools such as the pcodedmp disassembler. The oletools toolkit leverages the pcodedmp disassembler to detect VBA stomping by comparing keywords present in the VBA source code and p-code.[5][7]"
    }
  ],
